=begin
INPUT
a hash, with three keys
- price_min - value integer
- price_max - value integer
- name - value string - 
-- the string defines the manufacturer and product name divided by a space



RETURN 
A list of products where the products are hashes

Requirements 
- returned products must be within the price range submitted
- returned products must have the correct product name 
- price_min and price_max define a range of price, including the numbers themselves
- the specified value string to key symbol 'name' in the query hash can be lowercase and still return the correct result 

High Level Algorithm

First Select only products that satisfy the name requirement
Then Select only products from the first result that satisfy the price range requirement 



=end 

PRODUCTS = [
    { name: "Thinkpad x210", price: 220},
    { name: "Thinkpad x220", price: 250},
    { name: "Thinkpad x250", price: 979},
    { name: "Thinkpad x230", price: 300},
    { name: "Thinkpad x230", price: 330},
    { name: "Thinkpad x230", price: 350},
    { name: "Thinkpad x240", price: 700},
    { name: "Macbook Leopard", price: 300},
    { name: "Macbook Air", price: 700},
    { name: "Macbook Pro", price: 600},
    { name: "Macbook", price: 1449},
    { name: "Dell Latitude", price: 200},
    { name: "Dell Latitude", price: 650},
    { name: "Dell Inspiron", price: 300},
    { name: "Dell Inspiron", price: 450}
  ]
  
  query = {
    price_min: 240,
    price_max: 280,
    q: "thinkpad"
  }
  
  query2 = {
    price_min: 300,
    price_max: 450,
    q: 'dell'
  }

  # Pseudo Code
# Get name string from query
# define price_range from query
# Select products that includes name string when both strings are lowercase
# Select only products with a price included in the range 

  
  def search(query)
    name = query[:q]
    range = (query[:price_min]..query[:price_max]).to_a 

    PRODUCTS.select { |product| product[:name].downcase.include?(name.downcase) } 
        .select { |product| range.include?(product[:price]) }
  end
  
  p search(query)
  # => [ { name: "Thinkpad x220", price: 250} ]
  
  p search(query2)
  #  => [ { name: "Dell Inspiron", price: 300}, { name: "Dell Inspiron", price 450} ]
  
